Her sophomore follow-up, "My Life," earned a Grammy nomination, as did her 1996 album, "The Way I Should.", 1591=DeCant will soon set off on a December tour of New Zealand and Australia. She'll return stateside in the new year, and has dates booked through May 2014. On October 2, 2012, DeMent released her first album of original songs in 16 years, "Sing the Delta." It was recorded in Nashville, with an all-star supporting cast that included Bryan Owings on drums, Dave Jacques on bass, Al Perkins on pedal steel and Reese Wynana on B3 organ. Jim Hoke and Steve Herman also sat in as horn players. The project, of course, was heralded by fans and critics alike. Is there anything left to accomplish when a legend like Merle Haggard calls you, "The best singer I've ever heard"? There was for DeMent, whose songs like "Let The Mystery Be" and "Our Town" became ingrained in American culture, she simply kept plugging away.
